        "subject": "LU-8066 sysfs: properly handle failure of sysfs/procfs initialization",
        "message": "LU-8066 sysfs: properly handle failure of sysfs/procfs initialization\n\nWhile preparing for the move to sysfs I noticed that\ninitialization of procfs didn't handle most error\ncases. So this patch address those issues. Also the\nupcoming sysfs code will setup default attrs which\nwill come in three different flavors so add a flag\nso the proper struct attribute_group is used.\n\nChange-Id: I4045049bdf8dd2acc76b18ecbe65b26db0ed7b4b\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
